*monapo-20090423 (03 Jun 2015)

  03 Jun 2015; wjn <wjn@aol.jp> +metadata.xml, +monapo-20090423.ebuild:
  Add newly.

    "Most Japanese websites are designed for "MS P Gothic" font.
    'Monapo' font is a combined font that uses ipagp.otf (April 2009
  Ver.003.01)
   and mona.ttf.
    It has almost same width as MS P Gothic,
   so it can show Japanese Ascii Art properly."
    http://www.geocities.jp/ep3797/modified_fonts_01.html

